          "thumbnail_width": 480,
          "provider_name": "YouTube",
          "thumbnail_height": 360,
          "title": "2021 Ram 1500 TRX - crank up your speakers!"
        },
        "embedType": "video"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In addition to the powerful V8, the TRX was raised by two inches opening up space for the standard 35-inch tires, and the track width was increased by six inches requiring wider body panels â€“ the front fenders are eight inches wider, and the rear cargo bed panels have been widened as well. The ram air hood features cool-looking heat extractors, but sadly, the concept's side-mounted exhaust system didn't make it to the production design.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "These raised stance and modified body add up to an approach angle of 30.2 degrees, a breakover angle of 21.9 degrees, a departure angle of 23.5 degrees and a ground clearance of 11.8 inches. On top of that, the TRX has the ability to ford through more than 32 inches of water, while retaining its ability to tow up to 8,100 pounds... although not at the same time, obviously. The performance-tuned off-road suspension give the 2021 Ram 1500 TRX more than 13 inches of wheel travel at all four corners, and the Bilstein shocks allows the TRX to blast over terrain at speeds of more than 100 mph.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2020/08/2021-ram-1500-trx-7.jpg",
        "width": 670,
        "height": 445,
        "caption": "Image Credit: Fiat Chrysler Automobiles"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Ram gave the TRX a cabin fit for an off-road performance truck with a flat-bottomed steering wheel, massive paddle shifters and added technology such as Off-Road pages, a forward facing camera and a Baja drive mode. The TRX also got rid of the rotary shifter and gave the truck a proper center console mounted shifter, but it isn't clear if this will make its way to other Ram 1500 models.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Production of the 2021 Ram 1500 TRX starts in \"early fourth-quarter 2020\" with a ",
